 Weeks</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" cambria=\"cambria\" math\",serif;\"=\"math',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">⑫</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">】</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:medium;font-family:Cambria,serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">Face-to-face class</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">／</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">《</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">90&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">minutes</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">》</span></p>", ""], "第25回": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:medium;font-family:Cambria,serif;\"><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">【</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">Flex Hours</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">】</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:medium;font-family:Cambria,serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">Online class</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">（</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">On-demand format</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">）／《</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">20&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">minutes</span><span lang=\"JA\" ms=\"ms\" mincho\";\"=\"mincho';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">》</span></p>", ""], "授業計画1": "In taking this course, students will become more accustomed to using English in a variety of speaking tasks. While the Oral Presentation course focuses more on the preparation and delivery of academic speeches, this Speech Communication course takes a more general approach, mainly directed at the overall development of communication skills.<br /><br />This is a fun, but challenging course, in which students will constantly plan, practice and deliver both short and long speeches, either individually, in pairs, or in groups (depending on the class size). Speech activities in this course include but are not limited to role-playing, readers theatre, improvisation, oral interpretation, tongue twisters, story-telling, pecha kuchas, persuasive talks, and interviewing. The course outline is subject to change depending on the number of students who register for the course.", "授業外学習2": "Students will work outside of class to complete presentation slides, visual aids, presentation scripts, etc. Around 2-3 hours of weekly homework can be expected."}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["There is no required textbook for this course. The instructor will provide necessary materials."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Students’ evaluation of this course will be conducted in class, during the period designated by the university, making use of the standard evaluation form."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students1": ["各授業科目は、各学部・研究科の定めるディプロマ・ポリシー（DP）・カリキュラム・ポリシー（CP）に基づき、カリキュラム上に配置されています。DP・CPを意識して本授業科目の学修を進めることで、各学部・研究科の期待する能力が養成されます。各学部・研究科のDP、CPや教育課程表（授業科目一覧等）は、下記リンクこちらに掲載していますので学修計画の参考にしてください。https://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1※kwicへのリンクとなります（在学生のみ閲覧可）"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "Students’ final grade will derive from a combination of assignments, activities, presentations, etc."], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note Grades are from a combination of weekly assignments and presentations&nbsp;"], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年04月05日 00時21分55秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "春学期／Spring", "月曜６時限／Monday 6", "春学期／Spring", "ＯＣ１４０３"]}, "campas": 2, "name": "【500】スピーチ・コミュニケーション論　１／Speech Communication", "管理部署": 37, "単位数": 2, "担当者": "カバリ　ヴィヴィアン（KHAVARI VIVIAN BUSSINGUER） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "本登録", "開講期": 1, "時限1": 5, "時限1_term": 0, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\nGrades are from a combination of weekly assignments and presentations "}